name: Africa is Done Suffering [Black]
description:
[Image Description: Front] 
A silhouette of the continent of Africa. Within the border are text descriptions of problems that have hindered Africa. Poverty, abuse, rape, malnutrition, oppression etc. all shown in white writing. Overlaying these words in highlighter red is the acronym A.I.D.S. which hints at the deadliest disease in Africa, the acronym most importantly represents our movement Africa is Done Suffering.

[Image Description: Back] 
An explanation of the A.I.D.S. acronym in dark red and white font reading: Africa is Done Suffering. It’s a redefinition of this epidemic that has haunted our people for decades upon decades. The popular message of demise and trouble is converted into a message of hope; transforming a nightmare into a dream, a dream for a better tomorrow.
